03/05/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Representatives of the Western Balkan states -- Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Macedonia and Serbia-Montenegro -- sealed an agreement in Brussels on Tuesday (2 May) to open a regional school of public administration.
The EU will provide 1m euros.
Officials hope to open the school by the end of this year, though its location has not been announced.
(Fena, Makfax - 02/05/06)
